<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04564</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ENSURING THE EMPLOYEES' RIGHT TO THEIR WAGES, INCLUDING WAGE-RELATED SOCIAL SECURITY AND WELFARE BENEFITS, AMENDING FOR THE PURPOSE PRESIDENTIAL DECREE NO. 442, AS AMENDED, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE LABOR CODE OF THE PHILIPPINES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to increase penalties to impose stricter guidelines for the unjust employers who fail  to pay the required minimum wage rates including wage-related benefits.

Intends to insert Art. 97-A to P.D.442 which provides that every employee shall be covered by the SSS, the PHILHEALTH, the PAG-IBIG FUND, and other social security and welfare benefits; and notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, all premium contributions shall be shouldered by the
employer.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALVAREZ, PANTALEON D.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-09-12</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LABOR AND EMPLOYMENT ON 2019-09-16</td></tr></table>